80. Build a test cookie with the setcookie( ) function using PHP.
ANSWER
<?php
// Step 1: Set a test cookie (must be called before any HTML output)
setcookie("test_cookie", "CookieValue123", time() + 3600, "/"); // Expires in 1 hour
// Step 2: Display status
?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Test Cookie in PHP</title>
</head>
<body>
<?php
// Step 3: Check if the cookie is set on the next page load
if (isset($_COOKIE['test_cookie'])) {
    echo "✅ Test cookie is set. Value: " . $_COOKIE['test_cookie'];
} else {
    echo "ℹ️ Test cookie has been sent. Please refresh the page to check if it's set.";
}
?>
</body>
</html>

OUTPUT
 Test cookie has been sent. Please refresh the page to check if it's set.

